By Doris Esa  Abuja – The Federal Government on Friday launched the Nigeria Internal Security and Public Safety Alert System (NISPSAS) to assist the public access prompt response to emergencies and public safety. NISPSAS is an integrated and single mobile application developed to
assist citizens access prompt response to emergencies and public safety. The Minister of Interior, Lt.-Gen. Abdulraman Dambazau (Rtd), who
launched the System at the Ministry in Abuja, said the Mobile App is
linked to all the Services under the ministry to monitor their
activities. He said the App would enhance collaboration and cooperation among security imperatives. Dambazu said the Safety alert system is essentially to make everybody
contribute towards public safety, adding “the App is user friendly, you
can report any emergency”. The minister said the app could also be used for issues relating to
fire hazards, accidents on the highways and crimes as well as other
issues of public concern. (NAN)